                                      swim

simple macos window manager.

each option allows moving and resizing the focused window.

usage:

  swim [option]

available options:

  left         :  left half of the screen
  right        :  right half of the screen
  top          :  top half of the screen
  bottom       :  bottom half of the screen
  top-left     :  top left quarter of the screen
  top-right    :  top right quarter of the screen
  bottom-left  :  bottom left quarter of the screen
  bottom-right :  bottom right quarter of the screen
  center       :  center of the screen
  full         :  full screen

use a hotkey daemon (e.g. 'https://github.com/koekeishiya/skhd') to bind swim
commands to keyboard shorcuts.  the 'skhdrc-example' file contains an example
configuration for 'skhd'.
